Dear Raffaella,

Thank you for reaching out and sharing your concerns about the outcome of y=
our privacy request. We understand this process is important to you and app=
reciate the opportunity to assist further.

In response to your previous request, Tower provided all the personal infor=
mation we hold on record. This included:

  *   A comprehensive IT search using the prompts and variations you specif=
ied
  *   ShareFile logs
  *   The NotifyUs report from the Office of the Privacy Commissioner
  *   Explanations for any redactions
  *   All relevant correspondence (internal and external)

Below is the screenshot from your request made:
[cid:image003.png@01DC5F95.2639A4B0]

On 1 July 2025, you requested a full copy of your claim files, which we pro=
vided. Please note that correspondence does not necessary form part of clai=
m files, and at that time we did not include a full IT database search for =
communications. We have now completed a full system search for claim C90306=
256 and uploaded the additional correspondence to your folder, which you ca=
n access here: https://towernz.sharefile.com/d-sf8d9e0854e8947a3b0e4c249d82=
c2b01

Based on our searches, we believe we do not hold any further information co=
ntaining the wording =E2=80=9C23 Mays,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9C23 Mays Road,=E2=
=80=9D =E2=80=9CC90306048,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CC90306256,=E2=80=9D or any nam=
e variations in our systems.

Under Information Privacy Principle 6 of the Privacy Act 2020, we are requi=
red to provide access to personal information we hold. This obligation incl=
udes ensuring the information is meaningful and that providing it does not =
become unreasonable. Based on the steps taken, we believe the specific info=
rmation you are seeking either does not exist or cannot be located despite =
reasonable efforts.

That said, we would still like to help where possible. If you could clarify=
 or narrow down the exact details you are looking for, we will do our best =
to check again within the content already provided.

If you remain unsatisfied with our response, you have the option to lodge a=
 formal complaint with the Office of the Privacy Commissioner. Office of th=
e Privacy Commissioner | Submit a complaint<https://www.privacy.org.nz/your=
-rights/making-a-complaint-to-the-privacy-commissioner/complaint-landing-pa=
ge/?SecurityID=3D4263e8575b7718fb1f5bf0015055638884935eee>

Thank you for your understanding, and please let us know if you=E2=80=99d l=
ike to refine your request so we can assist further.

Warm regards,
[cid:image001.png@01DC5F8C.180AE6A0]
Privacy Team
Level 5, 136 Fanshawe Street,
PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142
