From: Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud.com<mailto:raffaellanz@icloud=
.com>>
Sent: Wednesday, 26 November 2025 4:22 pm
To: Privacy <Privacy@tower.co.nz<mailto:Privacy@tower.co.nz>>
Subject: Privacy Act 2020 =E2=80=93 Non-Compliance, Outstanding Disclosure,=
 and Breach Documentation Required

Kia ora Privacy Team, I=E2=80=99m writing regarding my Privacy Act request,=
 originally submitted on 1 July 2025, which remains incomplete and non-comp=
liant after several months, multiple partial disclosures, and repeated exte=
nsions. Under IPP6 of the

Kia ora Privacy Team,

I=E2=80=99m writing regarding my Privacy Act request, originally submitted =
on 1 July 2025, which remains incomplete and non-compliant after several mo=
nths, multiple partial disclosures, and repeated extensions. Under IPP6 of =
the Privacy Act 2020, I am entitled to access all personal information Towe=
r holds about me across all systems and formats, including information held=
 by Tower=E2=80=99s contractors or agents.

A brief chronology for clarity:


  *   1 July: Full-file Privacy Act request submitted.
  *   25 July: First ShareFile link received but was broken.
  *   12 September: Public link exposed my folder and another customer=E2=
=80=99s folder; only six heavily redacted documents were provided.
  *   25 September: Second disclosure provided but still incomplete and mis=
sing core categories.
  *   26 Sept =E2=86=92 13 Oct =E2=86=92 24 Oct: Timeframes moved several t=
imes without a lawful extension notice.
  *   20 October: Tower requested extension to 7 November, which I accepted=
 in good faith.
  *   7 November: A bundle was provided, but mostly reating exchanges with =
myself, duplicates and missing substantial categories of information.
  *   Since 1 July, Tower has provided broken links, a public ShareFile lin=
k that exposed another customer=E2=80=99s folder, incomplete document sets,=
 and multiple shifting deadlines. The 7 November release consisted mainly o=
f exchanges with myself, duplicates and did not include key categories of i=
nformation: limited internal emails, no Teams messages, no claim notes, no =
call logs, no IT-sourced data, limited contractor correspondence, and none =
of the communications referenced in my 10 October request. None of the item=
s identified in that 10 October request were included.

On 10 October, I also raised a privacy breach in which my full name and mob=
ile number were disclosed by Tower staff to ASUR NZ on 10 August without my=
 consent. I have not received the breach assessment, harm or serious-harm e=
valuation, any NotifyUs or OPC reference, or an explanation of the lawful b=
asis for the disclosure.

The repeated omissions, shifting deadlines, and removal of previously relea=
sed material raise concerns about whether my request has been handled in a =
complete, competent, and good-faith manner. The pattern of partial releases=
 also suggests that the search and disclosure process has not been conducte=
d in a complete or systematic way.

To complete this request, Tower must provide:


  *   All internal communications (email, Teams, chat, SMS, drafts, call no=
tes, internal tasks) that contain C90306048, C90306256, =E2=80=9C23 Mays=E2=
=80=9D, =E2=80=9C23 Mays Road=E2=80=9D, or any variation of my name.
  *   Communications to or from: Grant Metson, Bryan Strong, Megan Jensen, =
Kelly Mason, Chris Cornwall, Zach Pion, Sasha Cotterill, Arna Neems, Ross H=
aliday, lighthouse@tower.co.nz<mailto:lighthouse@tower.co.nz> the Privacy T=
eam, and any staff involved with my claims.
  *   All external communications with and among ASUR NZ, KCL Engineering, =
Hills Laboratory, forensic specialists, and any contractors or assessors en=
gaged by Tower.
  *   The full Lighthouse folder, including =E2=80=9CFW: Request for Clarif=
ication =E2=80=93 Re: 23 Mays Road =E2=80=93 progression of claims response=
. C90306048.pdf=E2=80=9D.
  *   All claim notes for both claims (previously supplied earlier in the y=
ear but omitted from the 7 November release).
  *   Notes, transcript and recording of the 13 October meeting with Ross H=
aliday, and all communications involving him or Arna Neems.
  *   The original dataset from IT Security and the categorised set created=
 on or around 16 October.
  *   Any internal instructions relating to how the Privacy Act response wa=
s compiled or limited.
  *   Tower=E2=80=99s full search methodology (systems, search terms, date =
ranges, limitations, and contractors consulted).
  *   All ShareFile and IT audit logs used to generate or share links.
  *   Full documentation for the 10 August privacy breach.
  *   Please provide the information above within 5 working days, confirm t=
he date by which Tower will deliver the full response, and provide the stat=
utory grounds for any redaction or withholding. Please also confirm that no=
 fees will be charged, and that all records, audit logs, backups, and contr=
actor-held information are preserved and that no automated deletion process=
es are active.

If Tower withholds any information, please provide a lawful refusal notice.

Ng=C4=81 mihi,
Raffaella

