<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white">Kia ora Privacy Team, I=E2=80=99m writing regar=
ding my Privacy Act request, originally submitted on 1 July 2025, which rem=
ains incomplete and non-compliant after several
 months, multiple partial disclosures, and repeated extensions. Under IPP6 =
of the<o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Kia ora Privacy Team,<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">I=E2=80=99m writing regarding my Privacy Act request=
, originally submitted on 1 July 2025, which remains incomplete and non-com=
pliant after several months, multiple partial disclosures, and repeated ext=
ensions. Under IPP6 of the Privacy Act 2020,
 I am entitled to access all personal information Tower holds about me acro=
ss all systems and formats, including information held by Tower=E2=80=99s c=
ontractors or agents.<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">A brief chronology for clarity:<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-=
alt:auto;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6">
1 July: Full-file Privacy Act request submitted.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=
=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;=
mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6">
25 July: First ShareFile link received but was broken.<o:p></o:p></li><li c=
lass=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:a=
uto;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6">
12 September: Public link exposed my folder and another customer=E2=80=99s =
folder; only six heavily redacted documents were provided.<o:p></o:p></li><=
li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6">
25 September: Second disclosure provided but still incomplete and missing c=
ore categories.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-=
top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6">
26 Sept =E2=86=92 13 Oct =E2=86=92 24 Oct: Timeframes moved several times w=
ithout a lawful extension notice.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" st=
yle=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l3 level=
1 lfo6">
20 October: Tower requested extension to 7 November, which I accepted in go=
od faith.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-al=
t:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6">
7 November: A bundle was provided, but mostly reating exchanges with myself=
, duplicates and missing substantial categories of information.<o:p></o:p><=
/li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bot=
tom-alt:auto;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6">
Since 1 July, Tower has provided broken links, a public ShareFile link that=
 exposed another customer=E2=80=99s folder, incomplete document sets, and m=
ultiple shifting deadlines. The 7 November release consisted mainly of exch=
anges with myself, duplicates and did not
 include key categories of information: limited internal emails, no Teams m=
essages, no claim notes, no call logs, no IT-sourced data, limited contract=
or correspondence, and none of the communications referenced in my 10 Octob=
er request. None of the items identified
 in that 10 October request were included.<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">On 10 October, I also raised a privacy breach in whi=
ch my full name and mobile number were disclosed by Tower staff to ASUR NZ =
on 10 August without my consent. I have not received the breach assessment,=
 harm or serious-harm evaluation,
 any NotifyUs or OPC reference, or an explanation of the lawful basis for t=
he disclosure.<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">The repeated omissions, shifting deadlines, and remo=
val of previously released material raise concerns about whether my request=
 has been handled in a complete, competent, and good-faith manner. The patt=
ern of partial releases also suggests
 that the search and disclosure process has not been conducted in a complet=
e or systematic way.<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">To complete this request, Tower must provide:<o:p></=
o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-=
alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo9">
All internal communications (email, Teams, chat, SMS, drafts, call notes, i=
nternal tasks) that contain C90306048, C90306256, =E2=80=9C23 Mays=E2=80=9D=
, =E2=80=9C23 Mays Road=E2=80=9D, or any variation of my name.<o:p></o:p></=
li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bott=
om-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo9">
Communications to or from: Grant Metson, Bryan Strong, Megan Jensen, Kelly =
Mason, Chris Cornwall, Zach Pion, Sasha Cotterill, Arna Neems, Ross Haliday,
<a href=3D"mailto:lighthouse@tower.co.nz">lighthouse@tower.co.nz</a> the Pr=
ivacy Team, and any staff involved with my claims.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=
=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;=
mso-list:l2 level1 lfo9">
All external communications with and among ASUR NZ, KCL Engineering, Hills =
Laboratory, forensic specialists, and any contractors or assessors engaged =
by Tower.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-al=
t:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo9">
The full Lighthouse folder, including =E2=80=9CFW: Request for Clarificatio=
n =E2=80=93 Re: 23 Mays Road =E2=80=93 progression of claims response. C903=
06048.pdf=E2=80=9D.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-mar=
gin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo9">
All claim notes for both claims (previously supplied earlier in the year bu=
t omitted from the 7 November release).<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNorm=
al" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2=
 level1 lfo9">
Notes, transcript and recording of the 13 October meeting with Ross Haliday=
, and all communications involving him or Arna Neems.<o:p></o:p></li><li cl=
ass=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:au=
to;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo9">
The original dataset from IT Security and the categorised set created on or=
 around 16 October.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-mar=
gin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo9">
Any internal instructions relating to how the Privacy Act response was comp=
iled or limited.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin=
-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo9">
Tower=E2=80=99s full search methodology (systems, search terms, date ranges=
, limitations, and contractors consulted).<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoN=
ormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list=
:l2 level1 lfo9">
All ShareFile and IT audit logs used to generate or share links.<o:p></o:p>=
</li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bo=
ttom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo9">
Full documentation for the 10 August privacy breach.<o:p></o:p></li><li cla=
ss=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:aut=
o;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo9">
Please provide the information above within 5 working days, confirm the dat=
e by which Tower will deliver the full response, and provide the statutory =
grounds for any redaction or withholding. Please also confirm that no fees =
will be charged, and that all records,
 audit logs, backups, and contractor-held information are preserved and tha=
t no automated deletion processes are active.<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
</div>
